# EtherAgent Environment Configuration
# ============================================
# This file shows all available environment variables
# Copy to .env.local and fill in your values
# 
# IMPORTANT: 
# - .env.local is ignored by git (see .gitignore)
# - constants.ts is ignored by git (contains sensitive data)
# - For Vercel deployment: Set these in Vercel dashboard
# - For local development: Copy this file to .env.local

# ============================================
# REQUIRED: AI Configuration
# ============================================
# Get your free API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# Required for EtherAgentAI to evaluate tasks
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ============================================
# BLOCKCHAIN: Sepolia Testnet (Development)
# ============================================
# Use these for testing on Sepolia testnet (FREE)
# Get free Sepolia ETH: https://www.infura.io/faucet/sepolia

# MNEE Token on Sepolia (Mock ERC20 for testing)
VITE_MNEE_TOKEN_ADDRESS=0x2E96901a92AB07a9Cf6D2570399eB1c71775A272

# TaskEscrow Contract on Sepolia (Your escrow contract)
VITE_TASK_ESCROW_ADDRESS=0x097cc5405702dd70116367a4b85158881E8253a0

# ============================================
# BLOCKCHAIN: Ethereum Mainnet (Production)
# ============================================
# Uncomment these for production deployment on mainnet
# MNEE Mainnet: USD-backed stablecoin
# See MNEE_MAINNET_SETUP.md for complete instructions

# Official MNEE stablecoin on Ethereum mainnet
# VITE_MNEE_TOKEN_ADDRESS_MAINNET=0x8ccedbAe4916b79da7F3F612EfB2EB93A2bFD6cF

# Your TaskEscrow contract deployed to mainnet
# Deploy using: https://remix.ethereum.org
# VITE_TASK_ESCROW_ADDRESS_MAINNET=0x[YOUR_MAINNET_ESCROW_ADDRESS]

# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT: Vercel Setup
# ============================================
# To deploy on Vercel:
# 
# 1. Create GitHub repo (make it PUBLIC)
# 2. Connect GitHub to Vercel (https://vercel.com)
# 3. In Vercel Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables, add:
#    - VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY = your_key
#    - VITE_MNEE_TOKEN_ADDRESS = contract_address
#    - VITE_TASK_ESCROW_ADDRESS = escrow_contract_address
#
# 4. Vercel automatically deploys on git push
#
# NOTE: constants.ts is NOT committed to git (see .gitignore)
#       Vercel reads environment variables at build time

# ============================================
# Notes
# ============================================
# 1. constants.ts reads from these env variables
#    Look at constants.ts for how values are loaded
#
# 2. For local development:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#    Edit .env.local with your values
#    Add to .gitignore: ✓ Already done
#
# 3. For Vercel:
#    - Commit .env.example (shows what's needed)
#    - DO NOT commit .env.local
#    - DO NOT commit constants.ts
#    - Set values in Vercel dashboard
#
# 4. For hackathon/production:
#    Use Ethereum mainnet with real MNEE
#    See MNEE_MAINNET_SETUP.md for steps
